============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is entropy?
A1: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q2: What is natural selection?
A2: Natural selection: individuals with traits better
     suited to their environment survive and reproduce more.
     Over many generations, these traits become more common
     in the population.

Q3: What is a programming language?
A3: A programming language is a formal set of instructions
     for computers. High-level languages (Python, Java) are
     human-readable; low-level (Assembly) are closer to
     machine code.

Q4: What is democracy?
A4: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

Q5: What is the periodic table?
A5: The periodic table organizes 118 elements by atomic
     number. Elements in the same column share chemical
     properties. Rows are periods; columns are groups.

